Description: Fragment of East Greek pottery closed vase, oenochoe or amphora. At top, black band with added red band lined in white; below frieze of goats browsing to right: leg and tail of one at right break, head of second on left; fringe fill above, large rosette between animals. Soft fabric with very fine mica inclusions.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.992)
